title: Independent candidate Bakht Muhammad wins PB-39 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Bakht Muhammad has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-39, Quetta-II by securing 6,618 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI-P) who bagged 5,878 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn out remained 34.47 per cent.
